  </ul>

  <h2>During Monsoon: Daily Management</h2>
  <p>
    When the rains arrive, shift to a more intensive management routine:
  </p>

  <h3>Increase Monitoring Frequency</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Test pH, DO, and salinity twice daily — early morning and late afternoon</li>
    <li>Monitor ammonia and nitrite every 48 hours, especially after heavy rain</li>
    <li>Check pond water level every morning — remove excess water slowly</li>
    <li>Observe shrimp behaviour and feeding activity at each feed time</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Adjust Feeding</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Reduce feeding by 30–50% during continuous rain and cloudy days</li>
    <li>Feed during cooler parts of the day when DO is more stable</li>
    <li>Use <a href="/products/feed-pond-preparers/gro-bind/">GRO-BIND</a> to prevent pellet disintegration in rain-softened water</li>
    <li>Watch feeding trays carefully — skip a feed if shrimp are not actively eating</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Water Exchange Strategy</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Exchange water slowly — rapid changes cause more stress than gradual shifts</li>
    <li>Exchange from the bottom to remove heavier saline water and accumulated sludge</li>
    <li>If source water is turbid, let it settle in a reservoir before adding to ponds</li>
    <li>Avoid exchanging during the heaviest rainfall — wait for conditions to stabilise</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Post-Monsoon Recovery</h2>
  <p>
    Once the monsoon tapers off, focus on restoring pond conditions for the remainder of the crop cycle:
  </p>

  <h3>Correct Water Parameters</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Apply W-SOFTENER to restore alkalinity and stabilise pH back to optimal range</li>
    <li>Use OXY-FARM to rebuild dissolved oxygen levels and support nitrification</li>
    <li>Test and correct salinity gradually — aim for changes of no more than 2 ppt per day</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Restore Beneficial Bacteria</h3>
  <p>
    Heavy rain dilutes probiotic populations and flushes out beneficial bacteria. Rebuild your biological filter:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Apply <a href="/products/probiotics-soil-care/pro-plus/">PRO PLUS</a> to restore soil health and degrade accumulated organic sludge</li>
    <li>Use <a href="/products/probiotics-soil-care/farm-pro/">FARM PRO</a> to re-establish water column probiotics and plankton balance</li>
    <li>Apply GASO CLEAN if ammonia or nitrite levels remain elevated after rain</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Support Stock Recovery</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Apply FARM-C+ for 3–5 consecutive days to boost immunity and improve feed intake</li>
    <li>Gradually increase feeding as water parameters stabilise and shrimp resume active feeding</li>
    <li>Monitor for disease signs — gill discolouration, lethargy, or erratic swimming — and treat promptly</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Monsoon Checklist Summary</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Pre-monsoon:</strong> Reinforce dykes, service aerators, stockpile W-SOFTENER, OXY-FARM, GASO CLEAN, FARM-C+</li>
    <li><strong>During monsoon:</strong> Test twice daily, reduce feeding, slow water exchange, apply treatments as needed</li>
    <li><strong>Post-monsoon:</strong> Correct parameters, restore probiotics, support stock recovery</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Monsoon does not have to mean losses. With the right preparation and discipline, you can protect your stock and come out of the rainy season with a healthy, harvest-ready crop. Our technical team is available to help you build a monsoon management plan specific to your farm's location and stocking density.
  </p>

